---
title: Butternut & Sweet Potato Soup with Bacon Note: Blender Required
description: For this harvest-inspired meal, you’ll whip up a pot of earthy-sweet butternut squash and sweet potato soup with just a touch of nutmeg. Blitz in the blender (required!) until smooth and creamy, then dollop with tangy crême fraîche and a shower of bacon-scallion-panko breadcrumbs for crunchy contrast and serve with garlic-lemon toasts for dipping.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66b14e6778d91450badf814d-3755b51c.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/66b14e6778d91450badf814d-en-US.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/butternut-sweet-potato-soup-with-bacon-66b14e6778d91450badf814d
nutrition:
  calories: 1050 kcal
  fat: 64 g
  saturated fat: 30 g
  carbohydrates: 94 g
  sugar: 22 g
  protein: 21 g
  fiber: 11 g
  sodium: 2410 mg
---

Wash and dry produce.

Heat a #medium pot{} (large pot for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add
@bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until
crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer
to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Reserve bacon fat in pot for use in Step 3.

Once bacon is cool enough to handle, roughly chop.

While bacon cooks, peel and dice @sweet potatoes{2} into 1-inch pieces. Trim and thinly
slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Pick sage leaves from stems; roughly
chop leaves. Zest and quarter @lemon{1} (for 4 servings, zest one lemon; quarter both).

In pot with bacon fat, melt 2 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon} over medium-high heat. Add sweet potatoes, @butternut squash{8%ounce},
scallion whites, half the @garlic powder{1/2%teaspoon},
@sage{1%tablespoon}, and @nutmeg{1/8%teaspoon} (2 TBSP sage and 1⁄4 tsp nutmeg for 4). Season with @salt{1%teaspoon} (11⁄2 tsp for 4) and a big pinch of @pepper{pinch}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies begin to brown, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in @water{1 1/4%cup} (21⁄2 cups for 4), @milk{1}, @chicken stock concentrate{2},
@vidalia onion paste{1/2%ounce}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} to pot. Bring
to a boil, then reduce heat to medium low. Cover and cook until veggies are tender,
stirring occasionally, ~{10-12%minutes}. Remove from heat.

Stir in juice from two lemon wedges (four wedges for 4); stir to combine.

== Panko Topping ==

While soup cooks, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a #small pan{} over medium heat. Add
@panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and toast, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Transfer panko to a #small bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Garlic-Lemon Toasts ==

Halve and toast @demi-baguette{1}.

While bread toasts, place 2 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4 servings) and remaining
@garlic powder{1/2%teaspoon} in a second #small microwave-safe bowl{}. Cover with
#plastic wrap{} and #microwave{} until butter has melted, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add lemon zest; season generously with @pepper{}. Stir to combine.

Brush garlic-lemon butter onto cut sides of toasted baguette. Halve on a diagonal.

== To Serve ==

Once veggies are tender, carefully transfer soup to a #blender{} (or #food processor{}). TIP: If
you have one, use an #immersion blender{} to puree the soup right in the pot!

Blend soup until no large pieces remain and mixture is smooth, ~{60-90%seconds}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{} to taste. TIP: To blend hot soup safely, work in batches
if needed, filling blender only halfway. To blend, remove center cap from blender lid,
secure lid on blender, and hold a folded #kitchen towel{} over the lid to allow steam to
escape and protect yourself from splatters.

To bowl with toasted panko, add bacon and scallion greens. Stir to combine.

Divide soup between #bowls{}. Top with bacon-scallion panko and dollop with
@crème fraîche{4%tablespoon}. Serve garlic-lemon toasts and remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.